ope scars. You call the circle and you let the writ speak first, and you hold your tongue until the murmurs tire themselves out against the iron of legal tone. When all is quiet, you tap the notice wall and tell the city that mercy can be commanded just this once so long as everyone remembers who asked for it and why.\", \"outcome\": \"The ceasefire holds because it must, and the relief barge moves under the weight of law as much as under the power of arms, and the city eats because the bells said to. The Wardens stand easy behind the armor of the writ and keep their dignity like a polished lantern, and Aren gives you a look that says he will pay for this leniency in reports but he is glad to write them. The Compact’s pride bristles but cannot argue with food in children’s hands, and Tavin Greel turns the moment into a story that says Kade Orrel made the bells remember the quays for once. The Veil honors the truce because breaking a writ would burn more than their masks, but a thin line of resentment is drawn under your name in a ledger that prefers debts paid in darkness. Your rewards come as promised, but they sit differently in your pockets, and you feel how heavy a city’s peace can be when it has the court’s seal pressed into it like a thumb on a bruise.\"}\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M3\"], \"next\": [\"M5\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"Faction Goodwill - Salted Compact\", \"description\": \"Assistance from two pilots in a future canal maneuver, earned as goodwill from the Salted Compact for keeping food moving without betraying their pride.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"Wardens Leniency Marker\", \"description\": \"A personal marker from Aren Mir that allows one checkpoint to be waved through, the sort of quiet mercy that is remembered in the Windward ledgers even if never spoken in parade.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"Smoulder Veil Truce Token\", \"description\": \"A limited promise of non-interference during one mission fro